SIMPLE: idolatrous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Idolatrous
<hw>I*dol"a*trous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of
or pertaining to idolatry; partaking of the nature of idolatry; given to
idolatry or the worship of false gods; <as>as, <ex>idolatrous</ex>
sacrifices</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Josiah] put down the <qex>idolatrous</qex> priests.</q>
<rj><qau>2 Kings xxiii. 5.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Consisting in, or partaking of, an excessive
attachment or reverence; <as>as, an <ex>idolatrous</ex> veneration for
antiquity</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Idolatrously</ent>⟦br⟧
